article.description: — Juan Munoz had 21 points as Longwood routed High Point 75-54 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Munoz scores 21 to lift Longwood past High Point 75-54
article.linkText: Munoz scores 21 to lift Longwood past High Point 75-54
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- — Juan Munoz had 21 points as Longwood routed High Point 75-54 on Tuesday night. Justin Hill had 15 points for Longwood (4-13, 3-8 Big South Conference). DeShaun Wade added 12 points and Heru Bligen had 11. Munoz made 6 for 8 3-pointers. Longwood dominated the first half, leading 44-21 at halftime. Both teams set season records for scoring in the first half. The Lancers’ 44 first-half points marked a season best, while the 21 first-half points for the Panthers were their lowest of the season. John-Michael Wright had 27 points for the Panthers (3-7, 1-4). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
